(2, 'img2.png', 'Spine Fracture', '12-09-2024', '<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(61, 142, 185);\">SPINE FRACTURE</span></strong></span></p>\n<hr style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(61, 142, 185); width: 50%; margin: 0 auto;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Spine fracture is a serious issues and defined as break in vertebrae and &nbsp;can affect the life like any other fracture.</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>SYMPTOMS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Patient with spine fracture usually presented with&nbsp;</span></p>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 50px;\">\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Back pain &ndash; most common complaint&nbsp;</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Difficulty &nbsp;to sit/stand/walk</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Sciatica like pain in limbs - radicular pain, tingling ,numbness</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Weakness in limbs</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Bladder/Bowel involvement usually - incontinence&nbsp;</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Spinal deformity and Change in posture &ndash; usually in case of untreated fracture.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">CAUSES</span></strong></p>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 50px;\">\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>In young patients&nbsp;</strong>&ndash; usually high impact injury &nbsp;i.e. road traffic accident, Fall from height/sports injury</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>In Old patients&nbsp;</strong>- Osteoporosis is leading cause. Because of low bone density over the time bone become vulnerable for fracture. Many time even leaning forward/sneezing trivial trauma may cause spine fracture.</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Fracture associate with &ndash;&nbsp;<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\n            <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Tumors &ndash; which usually metastatic</li>\n            <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Drug induced - e.g. long standing steroid consumption&nbsp;</li>\n        </ul>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>DIAGNOSIS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">&nbsp;On basis of clinical examination and investigations-</span></p>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 50px;\">\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">MRI &ndash; investigation of choice&nbsp;</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">X rays and CT scan&nbsp;</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Bone density -&nbsp;<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\n            <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">also called as BMD or DEXA scan</li>\n            <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">to quantity osteoporosis</li>\n            <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Kind of fixation during fracture fixation surgery</li>\n            <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Kind of medical management for osteoporosis</li>\n        </ul>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Management depends upon-</span></p>\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 50px;\">\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Cause of fracture</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Type of fracture&nbsp;</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Site of fracture</li>\n</ol>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Most of the time spine fracture don&rsquo;t need surgery and can be manage conservatively ( non surgical )</span></p>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 50px;\">\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Pain management with medicine</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Bracing of spine &ndash; it support back, improve overall strength and prevention of collapse of fracture</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Physical therapy- limbs and chest therapy to maintained joint suppleness and chest related issues when patient is in bed&nbsp;</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Treatment of associate factors- eg- osteoporosis</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>SURGERY&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Usually depend upon&nbsp;</span></p>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 50px;\">\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Failed conservative treatment&nbsp;</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Pain and disability increases despite of conservative treatment&nbsp;</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Nerve compression at time of presentation- weakness in limbs, bladder and bowel incontinence&nbsp;</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Deformity of spine</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>TYPES OF SURGERIES</strong></span></p>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 50px;\">\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>In young patient</strong> &ndash; mainly spinal fixation +/- decompression of neural elements</li>\n    <li style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>In old age&nbsp;</strong>- cementing of affected vertebrae- Balloon kyphoplasty /vertebroplasty &ndash; This is minimally invasive procedure. In this procedure special kind of cement to fill the void created after fracture. This procedure is with &nbsp; <strong><u>MAXIMUM BENEFIT WITH MINIMAL INTERVENTION.</u></strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(61, 142, 185);\"><strong>In some case need fixation need along with cementing.</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt 36pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">&nbsp;</span></p>', 'Spine fracture- Spine fracture is a serious issues and defined as break in vertebrae\r\nand can affect the life like any other fracture.\r\n', 'spine-fracture'),
(3, 'img3.png', 'Spine Tumors ', '23-09-2024', '<h2 style=\"text-align: center;color: rgb(229, 231, 235) rgb(229, 231, 235) rgb(0, 86, 179); font-size: 24px;font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\">SPINE TUMOR</span></h2>\n<hr style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(61, 142, 185); width: 50%; margin: 0 auto;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><br></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Spine tumors are abnormal growths that develop in or around the spinal cord and vertebrae. They can be <strong>benign (non-cancerous)</strong> or <strong>malignant (cancerous)</strong> and may originate from the spine itself or spread (metastasize) from other parts of the body.</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Types of Spine Tumors:</strong></span><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">.</span></p>\n<ol start=\"1\" type=\"1\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; padding-left:50px; margin-bottom:0cm;\">\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Vertebral Column Tumors</strong>: Affect the bones of the spine (vertebrae), which can be either primary (like osteosarcomas)</li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Metastatic tumor-&nbsp;</strong>A metastatic tumor of the spine refers to cancer that has spread (metastasized) from another part of the body to the bones of the spine or the spinal cord. The spine is one of the most common sites for bone metastasis, and cancers of the breast, lung, prostate, kidney, and thyroid are most likely to spread to the spine.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Common Characteristics:</strong></span></p>\n<ul type=\"disc\" style=\"padding-left: 50px; margin-bottom:0cm; list-style-type: disc;\">\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Location</strong>: Metastases usually occur in the <strong>vertebrae</strong> (bones of the spine) rather than the spinal cord itself. The thoracic spine is the most commonly affected region, followed by the lumbar and cervical regions.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Multiple Lesions</strong>: It is common for metastatic spine tumors to present as multiple lesions across several vertebrae.<span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Intramedullary Tumors</strong>: Develop inside the spinal cord, often gliomas or astrocytoma.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Extramedullary Tumors</strong>: Grow outside the spinal cord but within its protective covering. These include meningiomas and schwannomas</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Symptoms</strong></span></p>\n<ul type=\"disc\" style=\"padding-left:50px; margin-bottom:0cm; list-style-type: disc;\">\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Pain</strong>: Commonly in the back, neck, or at the site of the tumor, and can worsen with movement or at night.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Neurological Deficits</strong>: Numbness, weakness, difficulty walking, or loss of sensation.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Bowel or Bladder Dysfunction</strong>: Especially with tumors compressing the spinal cord.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Diagnosis</strong></span></p>\n<ul type=\"disc\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm; list-style-type: disc;\">\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Imaging</strong>:&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt 36pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">MRI - &nbsp;usually is &nbsp;primary investigations and commonly used to detect spine tumors .</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt 36pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">PET CT scan - Identifies the presence of multiple metastatic sites.</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt 36pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">CT scan - usually for detailed study and surgical planning.</span></p>\n<ul type=\"disc\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm; list-style-type: disc;\">\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Biopsy</strong>: A tissue sample may be taken to determine if the tumor is benign or malignant. in case of spine vertebral tumor it can be done as transpedicular biopsy usually done under local anesthesia/GA or CT guided biopsy.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Treatment:</strong></span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp; The goals of treatment for metastatic spinal tumors are often to relieve pain, improve or preserve neurological function, and maintain spinal stability. The treatment plan depends on the type and stage of the primary cancer, the extent of metastasis, and the patient&apos;s overall health.</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><br></p>\n<ul type=\"disc\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; margin-bottom:0cm;\">\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Medications</strong>:<ul type=\"circle\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; padding-left:50px; margin-bottom: 0cm; font-family: initial; font-size: initial;\">\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 10pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 2;\"><strong>Bisphosphonates</strong> and <strong>Denosumab</strong>: Help reduce bone destruction.</li>\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 10pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>Corticosteroids</strong>: Can reduce swelling and help with spinal cord compression.</li>\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 10pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>Pain Management</strong>: Narcotics or other medications for symptom relief.</li>\n        </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Radiation Therapy</strong>: Used to shrink or eliminate tumors that can&apos;t be fully removed surgically.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Chemotherapy</strong>: More often used for malignant tumors.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Targeted Therapy</strong>: For specific types of cancer, such as metastatic tumors.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Surgery</strong>: Often used to remove as much of the tumor as possible. Surgery is needed in case of neurological deficit / severe pain or need structural support of vertebral column.<ul type=\"circle\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; padding-left:50px;  margin-bottom: 0cm; font-family: initial; font-size: initial; line-height: 2;\">\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 10pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>Vertebroplasty/Kyphoplasty</strong>: Minimally invasive techniques that inject cement into the spine to stabilize weakened vertebrae. it stabilize the spine immediately and can obtain &nbsp;sample for biopsy simultaneously.</li>\n        </ul>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">The approach to treatment depends on the type of tumor, its location, and whether it is affecting spinal stability or neurological function.</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Prognosis:</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">The prognosis of metastatic spine tumors varies widely based on the type of primary cancer, the extent of metastasis, and the response to treatment. While metastatic spine tumors are generally not curable, early detection and appropriate treatment can improve quality of life and prevent serious complications like paralysis.</span></p>', 'Spine tumors are abnormal growths that develop in or around the spinal cord and vertebrae. They can be benign (non-cancerous) or malignant (cancerous) and may originate from the spine itself or spread', 'spine-tumors'),
(4, 'img4.png', 'Minimally Invasive Spine Surgery (MISS)', '10-10-2024', '<h2 style=\"text-align: center;color: rgb(229, 231, 235) rgb(229, 231, 235) rgb(0, 86, 179); font-size: 24px;font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\">Minimally Invasive Spine Surgery (MISS)</span></h2>\n<hr style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(61, 142, 185); width: 50%; margin: 0 auto;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Minimally invasive spine surgery (MISS) has revolutionized the field of spinal surgery, offering patients a less traumatic alternative to traditional open surgery. This innovative approach utilizes advanced techniques and technologies to treat various spinal conditions while minimizing damage to surrounding tissues. what minimally invasive spine surgery entails, the conditions it addresses, the techniques used, and the numerous benefits it offers to patients. For those seeking the <strong>best spine surgeon in Delhi</strong>, this approach is a game changer in modern healthcare.</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 107%;\">Understanding Minimally Invasive Spine Surgery</span></strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Minimally invasive spine surgery refers to a range of surgical techniques that allow surgeons to access the spine through smaller incisions compared to traditional open surgery. This approach is designed to reduce muscle and tissue damage, leading to quicker recovery times and less postoperative pain. If you&apos;re looking for the </span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><a href=\"https://bhupendrabharti.com/knowDoctor\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>best spine surgeon in Delhi</strong></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">, great option for safe and effective treatment.</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 107%;\">Key Characteristics of Minimally Invasive Spine Surgery</span></strong></span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-top:0cm; padding-left:50px;\" type=\"disc\">\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>Small Incisions</strong>: Surgeons make smaller incisions, often less than an inch long, which reduces trauma to the surrounding muscles and tissues.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>Use of Advanced Technology</strong>: MISS often employs specialized instruments, such as endoscopes and tubular retractors, to visualize and access the surgical site. Additionally, neuronavigation and robotic-assisted high-end microscopes are utilized to enhance precision and improve surgical outcomes.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>Enhanced Visualization</strong>: Surgeons may use fluoroscopy (real-time X-ray) or other imaging techniques to guide their instruments during the procedure, ensuring optimal precision.</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 107%;\">Conditions Treated with Minimally Invasive Spine Surgery</span></strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Minimally invasive spine surgery can be used to treat a variety of spinal conditions, including:</span></p>\n<ol style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-top:0cm; padding-left:50px;\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>Herniated Discs (Slip Disc)</strong>: When the herniated disc material inside a spinal disc bulges out, it can press on nearby nerves, causing pain and discomfort. The <a href=\"https://bhupendrabharti.com/knowDoctor\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>best spine surgeon in Delhi</strong></a> can use MISS techniques to remove the herniated portion with minimal disruption to surrounding tissues.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>Spinal Stenosis</strong>: This condition involves the narrowing of the spinal canal, leading to nerve compression. The <a href=\"https://bhupendrabharti.com/knowDoctor\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>best spine surgeon in Delhi</strong></a> can relieve this pressure with minimally invasive methods.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>Spinal Fusion</strong>: For instability or deformity, spinal fusion may be necessary. MISS allows the placement of bone grafts or implants through smaller incisions, promoting healing and stability.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>Scoliosis</strong>: This abnormal curvature of the spine can be corrected using minimally invasive techniques, reducing recovery time and postoperative pain.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>Spinal Tumors</strong>: Tumors located in or around the spine can be removed using minimally invasive methods, preserving as much healthy tissue as possible.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 107%;\">Techniques Used in Minimally Invasive Spine Surgery</span></strong></span></p>\n<ol style=\"padding-left:50px; margin-bottom:0cm;margin-top:0cm;\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>Endoscopic Surgery</strong>: A small camera (endoscope) is inserted through a tiny incision to visualize the surgical site, commonly used for herniated discs and spinal stenosis.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>Tubular Retractor Surgery</strong>: A tubular retractor creates a working channel for surgical instruments, ideal for spinal fusion and tumor removal.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>Robotic-Assisted Surgery</strong>: Surgeons use robotic systems for enhanced precision and control, applicable to various spinal procedures.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 107%;\">Benefits of Minimally Invasive Spine Surgery</span></strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Minimally invasive spine surgery offers numerous advantages over traditional open surgery, making it an appealing option for patients, especially those seeking treatment from the </span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><a href=\"https://bhupendrabharti.com/knowDoctor\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>best spine surgeon in Delhi</strong></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">. Key benefits include:</span></p>\n<ol style=\"padding-left:50px; margin-bottom:0cm;margin-top:0cm;\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>Reduced Pain and Discomfort</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<ul style=\"padding-left:50px; list-style-type: disc;margin-left: 80px;\">\n    <li style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Less tissue damage and smaller incisions result in significantly reduced postoperative pain.&nbsp;</li>\n    <li style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Patients experience faster recovery, allowing them to resume daily activities sooner, making the treatment both effective and economically viable.</li>\n</ul>\n<ol style=\"padding-left:50px; margin-bottom:0cm;margin-top:0cm;\" start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>Shorter Hospital Stays</strong>\n        <ul style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; margin-top: 0cm; font-size: initial; font-family: initial; color: initial;\" type=\"circle\">\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Many procedures can be performed on an outpatient basis, meaning patients can go home the same day.</li>\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">For surgeries requiring hospitalization, the stay is typically shorter compared to traditional surgery.</li>\n        </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>Lower Risk of Complications</strong>\n        <ul style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; margin-top: 0cm; font-size: initial; font-family: initial; color: initial;\" type=\"circle\">\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Smaller incisions lead to less blood loss during surgery, reducing the risk of complications.</li>\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Reduced exposure of internal tissues lowers the likelihood of postoperative infections.</li>\n        </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>Improved Outcomes</strong>\n        <ul style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; margin-top: 0cm; font-size: initial; font-family: initial; color: initial;\" type=\"circle\">\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Advanced techniques allow for precise targeting of the surgical site, leading to better outcomes.</li>\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Many patients report higher satisfaction due to reduced pain, quicker recovery, and improved functionality.</li>\n        </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong>Less Scarring</strong>\n        <ul style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; margin-top: 0cm; font-size: initial; font-family: initial; color: initial;\" type=\"circle\">\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 8pt; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Smaller incisions result in minimal scarring, offering cosmetic benefits for patients.</li>\n        </ul>\n    </li>\n</ol>\n<p><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 107%;\">Overall Summary</span></strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">Minimally invasive spine surgery (MISS) offers a less traumatic, more effective option for treating spinal conditions. With the expertise of <strong>Dr. Bhupendra Pratap Bharti,</strong> </span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\"><a href=\"https://bhupendrabharti.com/knowDoctor\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>the best spine surgeon in Delhi</strong></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(40, 50, 78);\">, patients can benefit from reduced tissue damage, minimal postoperative pain, and faster recovery times. MISS also shortens hospital stays, lowers the risk of complications, and minimizes scarring, making it an appealing alternative to traditional open surgery. As medical technology continues to advance, MISS is set to play an increasingly important role in spinal healthcare, especially for those seeking expert care in Delhi.</span></p>', 'Minimally invasive spine surgery (MISS) has revolutionized the field of spinal surgery, offering patients a less traumatic alternative to traditional open surgery. This innovative approach utilizes ad', 'best-spine-surgeon-in-delhi');
